Don&#39;t use full xpathes, it&#39;s bad practice. Try to use unique locators that point to your element instead.

In you case carousel has several items. Item&#39;s class is `carousel-item`.
When item appears in viewport, it gets additional class `active`.
So locator for current visible item is `.carousel-item.active`.

The only thing that left is button locator. Button is actually single `a` in container with some `href`.

Now we got full unique locator of active item and it is `.carousel-item.active a[href]`
```java
WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, 10);
driver.get(&quot;https://bluelinetourpackage.com/Web&quot;);

WebElement button = wait.until(ExpectedConditions.presenceOfElementLocated(By.cssSelector(&quot;.carousel-item.active a[href]&quot;)));
button.click();
```

